same period of time over and over again?

360
00:19:22,390 --> 00:19:23,790
I wonder if they exist.

361
00:19:24,190 --> 00:19:25,320
Martians.

362
00:19:25,460 --> 00:19:27,760
I kind of don't
want them to.

363
00:19:27,900 --> 00:19:32,090
They're probably a reserved people,
living underground.

364
00:19:32,270 --> 00:19:34,200
They're probably friendly.

365
00:19:34,330 --> 00:19:36,100
There's no guarantee
of that.

366
00:19:36,240 --> 00:19:40,570
I'm bored of this.
UFOs. Let's look for UFOs.

367
00:19:43,180 --> 00:19:46,740
Exactly what does
she want to do?

368
00:19:46,880 --> 00:19:49,310
Now what could
that be?

369
00:19:49,420 --> 00:19:52,480
If we could figure that out,
this would all be solved...

370
00:19:53,190 --> 00:19:55,990
Oh, how about
trying this out?

371
00:19:56,620 --> 00:19:59,350
Give Miss Suzumiya a sudden
embrace from behind,

372
00:19:59,530 --> 00:20:02,320
then whisper "I love you"
into her ear.

373
00:20:02,960 --> 00:20:04,990
And who would be
doing that?

374
00:20:05,130 --> 00:20:07,830
Is there anyone else who could
fill the role other than you?

375
00:20:07,940 --> 00:20:11,170
I'm exercising my right to veto.
In other words, I'm not going to.

376
00:20:11,270 --> 00:20:15,110
I guess it can't be helped.
All right, how about if I do it?

377
00:20:16,480 --> 00:20:21,410
I'm kidding. I'm lacking a certain
something for the role.

378
00:20:21,550 --> 00:20:25,680
And all that would do is cause unnecessary
confusion in Miss Suzumiya.

379
00:20:29,590 --> 00:20:31,350
Hey, Nagato,

380
00:20:31,660 --> 00:20:35,960
you were aware of this loop before
Miss Asahina said anything, right?

381
00:20:36,300 --> 00:20:37,190
Yes.

382
00:20:37,330 --> 00:20:39,800
If that's the case,
why didn't you say anything?

383
00:20:40,830 --> 00:20:43,530
It's my job
to observe.

384
00:20:44,240 --> 00:20:45,760
I see...

385
00:20:46,440 --> 00:20:47,960
All right!

386
00:20:48,140 --> 00:20:51,200
